# Coding & Delivery Rules

- Never guess how code works: before writing new code, verify whether the relevant implementation already exists and/or can be validated by checking the repo.
- Every code you create must be professional, clean, and ready for production.
- Prefer libraries/tools over implementing solutions by hand.
- Prefer simplicity over complexity. Refuse over-engineering.
- Ensure tests remain working after code changes

## Required sections for every code change

For any proposed code change, include these sections in your response:

## Tests review
- What tests to add or update
- How to run/verify them (using the repo’s existing tooling)

## README review
- What documentation to update (if applicable)
- What the updated README/doc should say at a minimum

- If the repo has no test setup or testing toolchain, ask before choosing a framework/library.
